## Stack
- Backend: Python 3.12+, FastAPI, httpx (async), tenacity (retries), Pydantic v2
- Database: Supabase PostgreSQL (ap-southeast-1), accessed from the backend via the
  `supabase>=2.4` async SDK (service role key) and from n8n via its Postgres node
- Orchestration: n8n Cloud (track technology — must be central)
- LLM: Gemini 3.1 Pro / Gemini 3 Flash via Google AI Studio (student credits)
- UI: n8n Chat Trigger (no Next.js, no React, no Tailwind)
- Deployment: Google Cloud Run ($300 credits)
- MCP Tools: Repomix (codebase context), Context7 (live library docs)

## Absolute Rules
1. Plane API calls go through service/plane_client.py only. No direct calls elsewhere.
2. All environment variables go in .env.agent with a placeholder in .env.agent.example.
3. Never hardcode credentials, API keys, or connection strings anywhere.
4. Plane API auth: header `X-API-Key`, token format `plane_api_<token>`. Rate limit: 60 req/min.
5. Plane uses "cycle" (not "sprint") in its internal API.
6. Plane's Cloud API uses `/work-items/` paths (not `/issues/`).
7. No frontend framework. n8n Chat Trigger is the UI. If a dashboard is added, use vanilla HTML served by FastAPI.
